olive oil
1 Carrot
½ Onion
1 packet Udon Noodles
1 packet Beef Mince
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet Korean Stir-Fry Sauce
1 packet Sweet Chilli Sauce
1 tsp vinegar (white  wine or rice wine)
½ tbs soy sauce
1 packet parsley

• Boil the kettle.
• Thinly slice carrot into sticks. Thinly slice onion (see ingredients).

• Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water.
• Cook udon noodles over medium-high heat, gently stirring with a fork to separate, until tender, 1-2 minutes.
• Drain, rinse and set aside.

• Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan over high heat.
• Cook beef mince (no need for oil!) and carrot, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Add shredded cabbage mix and stir until just wilted,
1-2 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then stir through Korean stir-fry sauce, sweet chilli sauce, the vinegar, soy sauce and a splash of water.
• Add cooked noodles and stir to combine.

• Divide sweet-chilli beef mince and udon noodle stir-fry between bowls.
• Tear over parsley to garnish. Enjoy!